## 13. Why this is attractive from an investor perspective

### 13.1 Controllability instead of only demo effect

The market is full of AI demos, but poor in AI systems that can be cleanly embedded into real processes. m-pathy addresses exactly this gap.

### 13.2 Platform instead of single feature

The architecture is modular and extensible. New extensions can be added as declarative programs. This creates platform logic instead of feature logic.

### 13.3 High connectivity

Through the separation of orchestration, process flow, domain logic, and execution, the system can serve different industries and use cases without rebuilding the core.

### 13.4 Deterministic governance

M13 gives the system an unusually strong governance character. This increases credibility for B2B, controlled processes, and risk adjacent applications.

### 13.5 Hybrid capability

m-pathy combines language AI with real backend execution. This is strategically stronger than pure content systems.

